{"nodes":[{"pos":[12,49],"content":"Compiler Error C3894 | Microsoft Docs","needQuote":false,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error C3894 | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,37]}]},{"content":"Compiler Error C3894","pos":[598,618]},{"content":"'var' : l-value use of initonly static data member is only allowed in the class constructor of class 'class'","pos":[619,727]},{"pos":[734,886],"content":"Static <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>initonly<ept id=\"p1\">](../../dotnet/initonly-cpp-cli.md)</ept> data members can only be used as l-values at their point of declaration, or in a static constructor.","source":"Static [initonly](../../dotnet/initonly-cpp-cli.md) data members can only be used as l-values at their point of declaration, or in a static constructor."},{"content":"Instance (non-static) initonly data members can only be used as l-values at their point of declaration, or in instance (non-static) constructors.","pos":[893,1038]},{"content":"The following sample generates C3894:","pos":[1045,1082]}],"content":"---\ntitle: \"Compiler Error C3894 | Microsoft Docs\"\nms.custom: \"\"\nms.date: \"11/04/2016\"\nms.reviewer: \"\"\nms.suite: \"\"\nms.technology: \n  - \"devlang-cpp\"\nms.tgt_pltfrm: \"\"\nms.topic: \"error-reference\"\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"C3894\"\ndev_langs: \n  - \"C++\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"C3894\"\nms.assetid: 6d5ac903-1dea-431d-8e3a-cebca4342983\ncaps.latest.revision: 10\nauthor: \"corob-msft\"\nms.author: \"corob\"\nmanager: \"ghogen\"\ntranslation.priority.ht: \n  - \"cs-cz\"\n  - \"de-de\"\n  - \"es-es\"\n  - \"fr-fr\"\n  - \"it-it\"\n  - \"ja-jp\"\n  - \"ko-kr\"\n  - \"pl-pl\"\n  - \"pt-br\"\n  - \"ru-ru\"\n  - \"tr-tr\"\n  - \"zh-cn\"\n  - \"zh-tw\"\n---\n# Compiler Error C3894\n'var' : l-value use of initonly static data member is only allowed in the class constructor of class 'class'  \n  \n Static [initonly](../../dotnet/initonly-cpp-cli.md) data members can only be used as l-values at their point of declaration, or in a static constructor.  \n  \n Instance (non-static) initonly data members can only be used as l-values at their point of declaration, or in instance (non-static) constructors.  \n  \n The following sample generates C3894:  \n  \n```  \n// C3894.cpp  \n// compile with: /clr  \nref struct Y1 {  \n   initonly static int data_var = 0;  \n  \npublic:  \n   // class constructor  \n   static Y1() {  \n      data_var = 99;   // OK  \n      System::Console::WriteLine(\"in static constructor\");  \n   }  \n  \n   // not the class constructor  \n   Y1(int i) {  \n      data_var = i;   // C3894  \n   }  \n  \n   static void Test() {}  \n  \n};  \n  \nint main() {  \n   Y1::data_var = 88;   // C3894  \n   int i = Y1::data_var;  \n   Y1 ^ MyY1 = gcnew Y1(99);  \n   Y1::Test();  \n}  \n```"}